  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nSending a large amount of HTTP requests has the ability to stall the beacon node and prevent it from performing its duties.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nN.A\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nRunning a beacon node with its http gateway server enabled, and sending in a large amount of requests at once. Ex: (Validator Status). Eventually the beacon node will be stuck in a deadlock. This can be mitigated by running ```--dev``` or ```--new-beacon-state-locks``` , which allows us to use the new state with improved state locking. \r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n![http_backlog](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33201827/86996344-00e30580-c1de-11ea-8e15-accbe6dfea94.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nUbuntu\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\nAlpha.13\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
